1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact sections 61-04-05.1, 61-16.1-53.1, and 61-32-08 of
2 North Dakota Century Code, relating to hearing and appeals processes of the department of
3 water resources.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 61-04-05.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 61-04-05.1. Comments - Hearing.
8 1. Comments regarding a proposed appropriation must be in writing and filed by the date
9 specified by the department of water resources under subsection 5 of section
10 61-04-05. The comments must state the name and mailing address of the person filing
11 the comments. Comment letters submitted electronically must state the name and
12 mailing address of the person filing the comments, and must be signed by the
13 submitter to be considered valid and part of the official record.
14 2. A person filing written comments also may request a public hearing for the department
15 to obtain additional information to evaluate the application or to receive public input by
16 the date specified by the department of water resources under subsection 5 of section
17 61-04-05. If a request for a public hearing is made and the department determines a
18 public hearing is necessary, the department shall designate a time and place for the
19 public hearing and serve a notice of hearing uponnotify the applicant and any person
20 who filed written comments. Service must be made in the manner allowed for service
21 under the North Dakota Rules of Civil Procedure by certified mail at least twenty days
22 before the hearing.
