1 3. If two or more municipal or public use permitholders request the public hearing to be
2 held locally, the department of water resources shall hold the hearing in the county
3 seat of the county in which the proposed water appropriation site is located.
4 4. The department of water resources shall consider all written comments received and
5 testimony presented at a public hearing, if held, and shall make a recommended
6 decision in writing. The recommended decision must be mailed to the applicant and
7 any party of record and may constitute:
8 a. Approval of all or a portion of the application, with the remainder held in
9 abeyance or denied;
10 b. Denial of the application; or
11 c. Deferral of the application.
12 5. Within thirty days of service of the recommended decision, the applicant and any party
13 of record who would be aggrieved by the decision may file additional written
14 comments with the department of water resources or request an adjudicative
15 proceeding on the application, or both. A request for an adjudicative proceeding must
16 be made in writing and must state with particularity how the person would be
17 aggrieved by the decision and the issues and facts to be presented at the proceeding.
18 If a request for an adjudicative proceeding is not made, the department shall consider
19 the additional comments, if any are submitted, and issue a final decision. If a request
20 for an adjudicative proceeding is made and the department determines an adjudicative
21 proceeding is necessary, the department shall designate a time and place for the
22 adjudicative proceeding and serve the notice of adjudicative proceeding uponnotify the
23 applicant and any person who filed written comments. Service must be made in the
24 manner allowed for service under the North Dakota Rules of Civil Procedure by
25 certified mail at least twenty days before the hearing.
