1 61-16.1-53.1. Appeal of board decisions - Department of water resources review -
2 Closing of noncomplying dams, dikes, or other devices for water conservation, flood
3 control, regulation, and watershed improvement.
4 1. The board shall make the decision required by section 61-16.1-53 within a reasonable
5 time, not exceeding one hundred twenty days, after receiving the complaint. The board
6 shall notify all parties of its decision by certified mail. Any aggrieved party may appeal
7 the board's decision to the department of water resources. The appeal to the
8 department must be made within thirty days from the date notice of the board's
9 decision has been received. The appeal must be made by submitting a written notice
10 to the department which must state specifically the reason why the board's decision is
11 erroneous. The appealing party also shall submit copies of the written appeal notice to
12 the board and to all nonappealing parties. Upon receipt of this notice the board, if it
13 has ordered removal of a dam, dike, or other device, is relieved of its obligation to
14 procure the removal of the dam, dike, or other device. The department shall handle
15 the appeal by conducting an independent investigation and making an independent
16 determination of the matter. The department may enter property affected by the
17 complaint to investigate the complaint.
18 2. If the board fails to investigate and make a determination concerning the complaint
19 within a reasonable time, not exceeding one hundred twenty days, the person filing the
20 complaint may file the complaint with the department of water resources within one
21 hundred fifty days of the submittal date of the original complaint. Without reference to
22 chapter 28-32, the department shall cause the investigation and determination to be
23 made, either by action against the board or by conducting the investigation and
24 making the determination.
25 3. If the department of water resources determines a dam, dike, or other device has
26 been constructed or established by a landowner or tenant contrary to title 61 or any
27 rules adopted by the board, the department shall take one of these three actions:
28 a. Notify the landowner by certified mail at the landowner's post-office address of
29 record;
30 b. Return the matter to the jurisdiction of the board along with the investigation
31 report; or
