1 c. Forward the dam, dike, or other device complaint and investigation report to the
2 state's attorney.
3 4. If the department of water resources decides to notify the landowner, the notice must
4 specify the nature and extent of the noncompliance and state that if the dam, dike, or
5 other device is not removed within a reasonable time as determined by the
6 department, but not less than thirty days, the department shall procure the removal of
7 the dam, dike, or other device and assess the cost of removal against the responsible
8 landowner's property. The notice from the department also must state that, within
9 fifteen days of the date the notice is mailed, the affected landowner may demand, in
10 writing, a hearing on the matter. Upon receipt of the demand, the department shall set
11 a hearing date within fifteen days from the date the demand is received. If, in the
12 opinion of the department, more than one landowner or tenant has been responsible,
13 the costs may be assessed on a pro rata basis in proportion to the responsibility of the
14 landowners. Upon assessment of costs, the department shall certify the assessment
15 to the county auditor of the county where the noncomplying dam, dike, or other device
16 is located. The county auditor shall extend the assessment against the property
17 assessed. Each assessment must be collected and paid as other property taxes are
18 collected and paid. Assessments collected must be deposited with the state treasurer
19 and credited to the contract fund established by section 61-02-64.1. Any person
20 aggrieved by action of the department under this section may appeal the decision of
21 the department to the district court under chapter 28-32. A hearing by the department
22 as provided for in this section is a prerequisite to an appeal.
23 5. If the department of water resources, after completing the investigation required under
24 this section, decides to return the matter to the board, a complete copy of the
25 investigation report must be forwarded to the board and must include the nature and
26 extent of the noncompliance. Upon having the matter returned to its jurisdiction, the
27 board shall carry out the department's decision under the terms of this section.
28 6. If the department of water resources, after completing the investigation required under
29 this section, decides to forward the dam, dike, or other device complaint to the state's
30 attorney, a complete copy of the investigation report must also be forwarded and must
31 include the nature and extent of the noncompliance. The state's attorney shall
